1
00:01:49,060 --> 00:01:54,580
=Eight Hundred=

2
00:01:58,140 --> 00:01:59,620
(Year 1995)

3
00:01:59,620 --> 00:02:01,220
If there are no problems, just sign it.

4
00:02:02,730 --> 00:02:05,860
Kaiming, technically,
as a technician here at the mine,

5
00:02:05,860 --> 00:02:08,020
(Agreement on Compensation for Termination of Labor Relations)
you aren't on the early retirement list.

6
00:02:08,020 --> 00:02:10,620
But you haven't really been
coming to work these past two years.

7
00:02:10,620 --> 00:02:12,410
The mine leadership
is in a difficult position.

8
00:02:13,580 --> 00:02:14,420
I know.

9
00:02:14,500 --> 00:02:15,430
Sir, but my...

10
00:02:16,220 --> 00:02:17,900
My wife just passed away.

11
00:02:17,900 --> 00:02:19,580
Please give me another chance.

12
00:02:19,580 --> 00:02:21,900
Your wife passed away two years ago.

13
00:02:21,900 --> 00:02:23,860
The factory has already
been very understanding.

14
00:02:23,860 --> 00:02:25,340
The factory is struggling now, too.

15
00:02:25,340 --> 00:02:26,860
There's really nothing we can do.

16
00:02:26,860 --> 00:02:27,740
Listen to me.

17
00:02:27,740 --> 00:02:28,820
Just sign it.

18
00:02:28,820 --> 00:02:30,040
At least you'll get some money.

19
00:02:37,460 --> 00:02:38,580
(Huo Kaiming)

20
00:03:00,260 --> 00:03:01,100
Who are you?

21
00:03:02,540 --> 00:03:03,420
I'm Huang Liang.

22
00:03:04,120 --> 00:03:05,380
I came here specifically to find you.

23
00:03:05,380 --> 00:03:06,260
I don't know you.

24
00:03:09,620 --> 00:03:10,460
I'm here...

25
00:03:11,540 --> 00:03:13,220
I'm here to offer you a job.

26
00:03:16,700 --> 00:03:18,620
You're a man who knows technology.

27
00:03:18,620 --> 00:03:19,460
At my place,

28
00:03:19,460 --> 00:03:21,100
I won't mistreat you.

29
00:03:22,260 --> 00:03:24,020
But there's one thing
I have to say upfront.

30
00:03:25,060 --> 00:03:26,420
I run an illegal coal pit.

31
00:03:26,420 --> 00:03:27,380
In Fengyang,

32
00:03:27,380 --> 00:03:29,500
you can't let anyone know.

33
00:03:29,500 --> 00:03:30,420
Eat up.

34
00:03:30,420 --> 00:03:32,900
After you finish eating,
I'll take you for a tour of the pit.

35
00:03:33,220 --> 00:03:35,260
Then, we'll go to the village
to find you a woman.

36
00:03:39,620 --> 00:03:42,100
This is the safety supervisor
of my mine.

37
00:03:42,100 --> 00:03:42,980
Tonight,

38
00:03:42,980 --> 00:03:45,340
just make sure you take good care of him.

39
00:03:45,340 --> 00:03:47,420
How about having
these two girls serve him together?

40
00:03:47,420 --> 00:03:49,260
I guarantee
your supervisor will be satisfied.

41
00:03:49,260 --> 00:03:50,820
You two had better be sharp.

42
00:03:51,780 --> 00:03:53,580
Hey, let's go get a massage.

43
00:03:53,580 --> 00:03:54,780
I know a lot of techniques.

44
00:04:15,700 --> 00:04:17,660
Are you new here?

45
00:04:17,660 --> 00:04:20,380
I haven't seen you before.

46
00:04:20,380 --> 00:04:23,300
Are you from Yunchuan, too?

47
00:04:23,300 --> 00:04:25,580
A fellow townsman!

48
00:04:25,580 --> 00:04:28,020
What's your name?

49
00:04:28,020 --> 00:04:29,540
Huo Kaiming.

50
00:04:32,860 --> 00:04:34,940
And what's yours?

51
00:04:34,940 --> 00:04:36,660
Jiao Yuqin.

52
00:04:47,780 --> 00:04:53,660
(Three months later)

53
00:05:01,620 --> 00:05:03,260
Try drinking some of this.

54
00:05:07,900 --> 00:05:09,540
Be good.

55
00:05:13,060 --> 00:05:15,300
Kaiming,

56
00:05:15,300 --> 00:05:16,940
I'm pregnant.

57
00:05:19,260 --> 00:05:21,780
What did you say?

58
00:05:21,780 --> 00:05:23,740
I'm pregnant.

59
00:05:23,740 --> 00:05:24,740
Do you

60
00:05:24,740 --> 00:05:26,260
not want it?

61
00:05:27,780 --> 00:05:29,300
Of course I want it.

62
00:05:29,300 --> 00:05:31,340
I've been married for so many years
and never had a child.

63
00:05:31,340 --> 00:05:33,820
I thought no one would be there
to take care of me in my old age.

64
00:05:33,820 --> 00:05:35,340
I'm so happy.

65
00:05:37,100 --> 00:05:38,540
Then,

66
00:05:38,540 --> 00:05:39,580
will you marry me?

67
00:05:42,300 --> 00:05:43,220
I will.

68
00:05:43,220 --> 00:05:44,620
We'll go register tomorrow.

69
00:05:44,620 --> 00:05:45,460
Good.

70
00:05:45,460 --> 00:05:46,620
I have a house here.

71
00:05:46,620 --> 00:05:47,460
I'll provide for you.

72
00:05:49,300 --> 00:05:51,500
I don't want to stay in Fengyang anymore.

73
00:05:51,500 --> 00:05:52,580
Why?

74
00:05:52,580 --> 00:05:54,580
Doing the work I do,

75
00:05:54,580 --> 00:05:56,020
everyone around here knows me.

76
00:05:57,300 --> 00:05:58,900
If people see me

77
00:05:58,900 --> 00:06:00,740
out on the street later on,

78
00:06:00,740 --> 00:06:02,660
what will the child do?

79
00:06:02,660 --> 00:06:03,620
Then, what should we do?

80
00:06:05,060 --> 00:06:07,900
Come back to Yunchuan with me.

81
00:06:07,900 --> 00:06:09,020
In the past two years,

82
00:06:09,020 --> 00:06:10,260
I've saved a bit of money.

83
00:06:10,260 --> 00:06:12,660
We can borrow
a little more from relatives.

84
00:06:12,660 --> 00:06:14,540
We can start a small business.

85
00:06:14,540 --> 00:06:16,020
No matter how hard life gets,

86
00:06:16,020 --> 00:06:18,060
as long as our family
is together, it's fine.

87
00:06:18,060 --> 00:06:18,900
Alright.

88
00:06:20,020 --> 00:06:21,900
I'll sell the house here.

89
00:06:21,900 --> 00:06:23,900
That way we'll have money
for the business too.

90
00:06:23,900 --> 00:06:24,780
Good.

91
00:06:24,950 --> 00:06:25,850
That's wonderful.

92
00:06:25,850 --> 00:06:27,320
I'm finally having a baby.

93
00:06:27,980 --> 00:06:28,820
That's wonderful!

94
00:06:30,620 --> 00:06:31,900
This is the money from the house.

95
00:06:33,220 --> 00:06:34,860
Work one more month,

96
00:06:34,860 --> 00:06:36,660
and once I get my salary,

97
00:06:36,660 --> 00:06:37,920
we'll go back to Yunchuan.

98
00:06:38,270 --> 00:06:39,140
You're not eating?

99
00:06:39,140 --> 00:06:40,620
There's no time.
I'm going down the shaft.

100
00:06:41,220 --> 00:06:42,060
Wait a moment.

101
00:06:43,020 --> 00:06:45,060
Drink your medicine before you go down.

102
00:06:45,060 --> 00:06:46,340
Oh, right.

103
00:06:46,340 --> 00:06:47,460
Take this too.

104
00:06:47,460 --> 00:06:48,420
What is this?

105
00:06:48,420 --> 00:06:50,260
It's also for your bronchitis.

106
00:06:50,260 --> 00:06:51,820
Take these two together.

107
00:06:51,820 --> 00:06:53,180
It'll be good for your throat.

108
00:06:55,020 --> 00:06:56,740
You're so good to me.

109
00:06:56,740 --> 00:06:58,180
This medicine

110
00:06:58,180 --> 00:07:00,260
really pips me up after drinking it.

111
00:07:00,260 --> 00:07:01,500
Is that so?

112
00:07:13,140 --> 00:07:14,010
Mr. Huo!

113
00:07:14,010 --> 00:07:18,100
=Episode 5=
(Death Benefit Bride)

114
00:07:21,740 --> 00:07:22,820
That's impossible.

115
00:07:24,580 --> 00:07:25,900
This medicine shouldn't do that.

116
00:07:28,180 --> 00:07:30,100
She added something to it.

117
00:07:30,100 --> 00:07:32,900
She said it was medicine for bronchitis.

118
00:07:32,900 --> 00:07:34,080
Bronchitis medicine?

119
00:07:34,440 --> 00:07:35,300
Liar.

120
00:07:35,300 --> 00:07:37,420
You must have bewitched her.

121
00:07:37,420 --> 00:07:38,900
You scum

122
00:07:38,900 --> 00:07:40,660
who sell drugs!

123
00:07:40,660 --> 00:07:41,700
Mr. Huo,

124
00:07:41,700 --> 00:07:43,700
don't get so worked up.

125
00:07:43,700 --> 00:07:45,780
You said Jiao Yuqin

126
00:07:45,780 --> 00:07:47,410
gave you the medicine in a bottle?

127
00:07:47,690 --> 00:07:48,540
How else?

128
00:07:48,540 --> 00:07:52,340
Otherwise, how would I know
the medicine in your bag was this kind?

129
00:07:53,460 --> 00:07:56,300
Since last year, I haven't allowed those
who take goods from me

130
00:07:56,300 --> 00:07:57,460
to sell them by the bottle.

131
00:07:57,460 --> 00:07:58,500
A couple of days ago, I saw

132
00:07:58,500 --> 00:08:00,820
someone holding a whole bottle.

133
00:08:00,820 --> 00:08:03,100
Are you talking about the person
who was burned to death at Beimianling?

134
00:08:03,100 --> 00:08:04,340
None of your business.

135
00:08:06,420 --> 00:08:07,580
Just tell me,

136
00:08:08,540 --> 00:08:10,280
when can you find her?

137
00:08:10,400 --> 00:08:11,330
Why do you

138
00:08:11,330 --> 00:08:12,620
insist on finding her?

139
00:08:12,620 --> 00:08:14,820
Even if I find her for you,
what could you possibly do?

140
00:08:19,020 --> 00:08:20,420
For every one I find,

141
00:08:21,540 --> 00:08:23,020
I'll kill one.

142
00:08:25,660 --> 00:08:27,660
Everyone who lied to me

143
00:08:32,820 --> 00:08:34,300
must die.

144
00:09:10,660 --> 00:09:11,660
Did Chen Hui send you?

145
00:09:13,780 --> 00:09:15,180
The person has been contacted.

146
00:09:16,700 --> 00:09:17,860
Are you sure it's him?

147
00:09:18,900 --> 00:09:19,740
Positive.

148
00:09:20,980 --> 00:09:21,900
What's this for?

149
00:09:22,700 --> 00:09:25,020
When he arrives,
it'll be easier to contact you.

150
00:09:30,860 --> 00:09:31,700
Where's Jiao Yuqin?

151
00:09:34,580 --> 00:09:35,460
(Yingxiong Welcomes You)

152
00:09:35,460 --> 00:09:37,340
(Yingxiong Roller Skating Rink)

153
00:09:40,260 --> 00:09:44,510
♪Perhaps there are
too many things I don't understand♪

154
00:09:45,050 --> 00:09:47,480
♪Maybe it's my fault♪

155
00:09:49,870 --> 00:09:53,870
♪Perhaps everything
has slowly passed us by♪

156
00:09:54,690 --> 00:09:57,100
♪Maybe there's no need to say more♪

157
00:09:59,140 --> 00:10:03,100
♪Never thought
you and I would end like this♪

158
00:10:05,340 --> 00:10:06,180
What is this?

159
00:10:06,980 --> 00:10:07,820
Give me the bag.

160
00:10:10,100 --> 00:10:10,940
What are you doing?

161
00:10:10,940 --> 00:10:12,810
You sold the medicine
to Jiao Yuqin, didn't you?

162
00:10:12,820 --> 00:10:14,030
Are you crazy? Who's Jiao Yuqin?

163
00:10:14,030 --> 00:10:14,910
- I don't know her.
- Is it you?

164
00:10:14,910 --> 00:10:17,070
Keep your voice down!
I'm telling you, give it to me!

165
00:10:21,150 --> 00:10:22,020
What are you doing?

166
00:10:22,020 --> 00:10:22,960
I won't give it to you.

167
00:10:26,720 --> 00:10:29,690
♪Maybe there's no need to say more♪

168
00:10:31,460 --> 00:10:35,360
♪Never thought
you and I would end like this♪

169
00:10:36,470 --> 00:10:38,870
♪No certainty in my heart♪

170
00:10:40,140 --> 00:10:45,340
♪Just remembering the promises we made♪

171
00:10:45,970 --> 00:10:49,270
♪Time and again, those impulses♪

172
00:10:50,710 --> 00:10:54,580
♪Don't break my heart, be gentle again♪

173
00:10:55,110 --> 00:10:59,180
♪I don't want to see your silence♪

174
00:12:31,380 --> 00:12:33,500
Tell me what you saw at the time.

175
00:12:33,500 --> 00:12:34,900
I went to a friend's house tonight,

176
00:12:34,900 --> 00:12:36,380
and I was coming back a bit late.

177
00:12:36,380 --> 00:12:37,780
Just as I reached the road ahead,

178
00:12:37,780 --> 00:12:39,120
I saw a fire over here.

179
00:12:39,240 --> 00:12:40,140
I rushed over to check,

180
00:12:40,140 --> 00:12:41,140
and I found

181
00:12:41,140 --> 00:12:42,080
someone lying inside.

182
00:12:42,230 --> 00:12:43,180
It scared me to death.

183
00:12:43,180 --> 00:12:44,740
I called the police immediately.

184
00:12:44,740 --> 00:12:46,820
Did you see anyone else at the time?

185
00:12:46,820 --> 00:12:47,660
No.

186
00:12:53,940 --> 00:12:54,780
Chief Liu.

187
00:12:55,140 --> 00:12:56,080
What's the situation at the scene?

188
00:12:56,090 --> 00:12:57,540
The body was already
charred when we arrived.

189
00:12:57,540 --> 00:12:58,410
Master.

190
00:12:58,410 --> 00:13:00,100
Did you record the statement
of the person who reported it?

191
00:13:00,100 --> 00:13:00,980
Yes.

192
00:13:00,980 --> 00:13:03,410
Master, could this be related to
the Beimianling body-burning homicide?

193
00:13:04,100 --> 00:13:05,780
It's hard to say right now.

194
00:13:05,780 --> 00:13:07,100
This is the second body-burning homicide

195
00:13:07,100 --> 00:13:09,620
in Fengyang Town
in a short period of time.

196
00:13:09,620 --> 00:13:11,500
We'll have to wait
for the autopsy results.

197
00:13:11,500 --> 00:13:13,140
I contacted Tang before I came.

198
00:13:13,140 --> 00:13:14,740
She'll arrive
tomorrow morning at the earliest.

199
00:13:14,740 --> 00:13:15,740
We need to find a place

200
00:13:15,740 --> 00:13:17,540
to preserve the body first.

201
00:13:17,540 --> 00:13:18,940
Limin,

202
00:13:18,940 --> 00:13:21,340
hurry up and contact the mortuary
at the Workers' Hospital.

203
00:13:21,340 --> 00:13:22,180
Okay.

204
00:13:23,380 --> 00:13:24,220
Easy does it.

205
00:13:39,060 --> 00:13:41,700
Based on these blood spatters,

206
00:13:41,700 --> 00:13:42,900
the killer should have

207
00:13:42,900 --> 00:13:44,100
stabbed the victim here

208
00:13:44,100 --> 00:13:45,180
and burned the body.

209
00:13:46,180 --> 00:13:47,420
So you're saying

210
00:13:47,420 --> 00:13:49,060
the body was moved?

211
00:13:49,060 --> 00:13:50,140
Look.

212
00:13:50,140 --> 00:13:51,610
There are clear drag marks here.

213
00:13:52,100 --> 00:13:52,970
It means someone

214
00:13:52,970 --> 00:13:54,100
dragged the body over.

215
00:13:56,060 --> 00:13:57,340
That's what I don't understand.

216
00:13:58,500 --> 00:14:01,380
If the killer murdered him there,

217
00:14:01,380 --> 00:14:03,180
why drag him all the way here?

218
00:14:03,180 --> 00:14:04,500
It doesn't look like the killer's doing.

219
00:14:04,500 --> 00:14:05,340
Look.

220
00:14:05,340 --> 00:14:08,020
The plants in this area
show clear signs of being burned.

221
00:14:09,260 --> 00:14:10,820
But the area around the body doesn't.

222
00:14:11,870 --> 00:14:12,760
This person likely

223
00:14:12,760 --> 00:14:14,180
wanted to pull him out of the fire.

224
00:14:15,020 --> 00:14:16,820
So there was a third person at the scene?

225
00:14:18,820 --> 00:14:20,620
As long as we find the third person,

226
00:14:20,620 --> 00:14:22,460
we'll know who the killer is.

227
00:14:40,520 --> 00:14:41,710
What's wrong with your eyelid?

228
00:14:44,140 --> 00:14:46,100
It keeps twitching.

229
00:14:46,100 --> 00:14:47,420
Sticking something on it.

230
00:15:01,140 --> 00:15:02,140
It's potassium manganate.

231
00:15:02,140 --> 00:15:04,100
It's the same as
what was on Yu Susu's body.

232
00:15:04,100 --> 00:15:04,980
Anything else?

233
00:15:05,980 --> 00:15:07,340
Fingerprints are a no-go.

234
00:15:07,340 --> 00:15:09,400
The autopsy will have to be done
back at the municipal PSB.

235
00:15:12,220 --> 00:15:13,060
Wait.

236
00:15:14,380 --> 00:15:15,220
Forceps.

237
00:15:26,420 --> 00:15:27,940
Master,

238
00:15:27,940 --> 00:15:29,140
this is a pager casing.

239
00:15:30,820 --> 00:15:31,980
Chief Liu,

240
00:15:31,980 --> 00:15:33,780
we can find

241
00:15:33,780 --> 00:15:35,380
the third person from the scene now.

242
00:15:41,940 --> 00:15:43,270
(Buying Pagers
and Cell Phones at High Prices)

243
00:15:43,270 --> 00:15:44,920
Boss, I have a pager here.

244
00:15:45,020 --> 00:15:46,060
See if you can take it.

245
00:15:53,740 --> 00:15:55,700
I can't guarantee it can be reconnected.

246
00:15:55,700 --> 00:15:56,580
Anyway, I found it.

247
00:15:56,620 --> 00:15:57,680
Just give me what you can.

248
00:15:57,690 --> 00:15:59,020
I'll call a friend over to take a look.

249
00:15:59,020 --> 00:15:59,950
He's an expert.

250
00:15:59,950 --> 00:16:01,220
If this thing is good,

251
00:16:01,220 --> 00:16:02,380
he'll even pay a higher price.

252
00:16:05,630 --> 00:16:06,500
Chen?

253
00:16:06,500 --> 00:16:08,110
It's me, Sun,
from behind the Commercial Building.

254
00:16:08,740 --> 00:16:10,020
Aren't you buying those

255
00:16:10,020 --> 00:16:11,580
pagers that can't be transferred?

256
00:16:11,580 --> 00:16:13,340
I have a young fellow here who has one.

257
00:16:13,340 --> 00:16:14,860
Why don't you
come over and check it out?

258
00:16:14,860 --> 00:16:15,740
Keep him there.

259
00:16:15,740 --> 00:16:16,740
I'll be right there.

260
00:16:16,740 --> 00:16:17,820
Wait for me.

261
00:16:17,820 --> 00:16:18,660
Okay.

262
00:16:30,060 --> 00:16:31,300
How much longer for your friend?

263
00:16:32,420 --> 00:16:33,380
Almost here.

264
00:16:33,380 --> 00:16:34,580
Any minute now.

265
00:16:34,580 --> 00:16:35,740
I'm not selling it today.

266
00:16:35,740 --> 00:16:36,580
Wait a bit longer.

267
00:16:43,220 --> 00:16:44,440
Where did the pager come from?

268
00:16:44,700 --> 00:16:45,580
I found it.

269
00:16:45,580 --> 00:16:46,700
Think carefully!

270
00:16:47,220 --> 00:16:48,230
I really found it.

271
00:16:48,300 --> 00:16:49,180
Really.

272
00:16:49,180 --> 00:16:50,020
Not talking, are you?

273
00:16:52,500 --> 00:16:53,340
What's going on?

274
00:16:54,660 --> 00:16:56,300
This really has nothing to do with me.

275
00:16:56,300 --> 00:16:57,310
It really has nothing to do with me.

276
00:16:57,310 --> 00:16:58,200
I didn't kill him.

277
00:16:58,200 --> 00:16:59,600
I really didn't kill Lu Yuan.

278
00:17:00,100 --> 00:17:01,180
I really didn't kill him.

279
00:17:05,540 --> 00:17:06,420
I really didn't.

280
00:17:06,420 --> 00:17:09,100
How did you know
the one who died was Lu Yuan?

281
00:17:10,260 --> 00:17:11,100
Speak!

282
00:17:12,740 --> 00:17:14,020
What exactly happened?

283
00:17:14,020 --> 00:17:14,860
Yuan.

284
00:17:16,260 --> 00:17:17,490
The brat called me.

285
00:17:17,780 --> 00:17:18,900
I'm going to get the money.

286
00:17:18,900 --> 00:17:20,700
You have to come with me.

287
00:17:20,700 --> 00:17:22,100
What am I going for?

288
00:17:22,100 --> 00:17:22,940
I suspect this brat

289
00:17:22,940 --> 00:17:24,820
is going to play dirty with me again.

290
00:17:24,820 --> 00:17:26,460
Don't you remember
he did that last time?

291
00:17:26,460 --> 00:17:27,940
You just find a place to hide.

292
00:17:27,940 --> 00:17:28,940
If things go wrong,

293
00:17:28,940 --> 00:17:29,940
you just shout loudly.

294
00:17:29,940 --> 00:17:32,260
After it's done, I'll give you 2,000 yuan.

295
00:17:33,020 --> 00:17:33,860
Later,

296
00:17:33,860 --> 00:17:35,700
I hid in the bushes.

297
00:17:35,700 --> 00:17:37,510
I thought if anything happened,
I'd rush out.

298
00:17:37,720 --> 00:17:40,300
But I didn't expect that person to just
kill Lu Yuan right away.

299
00:17:40,300 --> 00:17:41,180
Then, he poured

300
00:17:41,180 --> 00:17:42,500
something on him.

301
00:17:42,500 --> 00:17:44,140
The fire just erupted.

302
00:17:44,140 --> 00:17:45,220
When the fire first started,

303
00:17:45,220 --> 00:17:46,580
it was even purple.

304
00:17:46,580 --> 00:17:49,180
I didn't dare come out
until the man drove away.

305
00:17:56,860 --> 00:17:58,420
I wanted to save him,

306
00:17:58,420 --> 00:18:00,020
but the fire was just too big.

307
00:18:00,020 --> 00:18:00,860
So I...

308
00:18:10,980 --> 00:18:12,940
Did you see what the killer looked like?

309
00:18:12,940 --> 00:18:14,220
That day,

310
00:18:14,220 --> 00:18:15,780
his headlights were so bright

311
00:18:15,780 --> 00:18:17,500
that I could only see a silhouette.

312
00:18:17,500 --> 00:18:19,340
He seemed a bit taller than Lu Yuan,

313
00:18:19,340 --> 00:18:21,380
but I really couldn't see anything else.

314
00:18:21,380 --> 00:18:23,740
Could you see what car it was?

315
00:18:23,740 --> 00:18:25,090
It seemed to be a red sedan.

316
00:18:25,380 --> 00:18:26,260
Yes.

317
00:18:26,260 --> 00:18:27,110
A red sedan.

318
00:18:27,540 --> 00:18:29,100
How did you know Lu Yuan?

319
00:18:29,100 --> 00:18:31,820
We met at the video hall.

320
00:18:31,820 --> 00:18:33,780
He often watched videos alone.

321
00:18:33,780 --> 00:18:34,910
He looked pretty lonely,

322
00:18:35,220 --> 00:18:36,570
so I thought I'd keep him company.

323
00:18:36,900 --> 00:18:38,010
Tell the truth.

324
00:18:38,380 --> 00:18:39,500
I am.

325
00:18:42,340 --> 00:18:43,940
He was a tube popsicle vendor.

326
00:18:43,940 --> 00:18:45,340
I always bought them from him,

327
00:18:45,340 --> 00:18:46,860
and we often ate them together.

328
00:18:46,860 --> 00:18:47,700
That's how we met.

329
00:18:49,620 --> 00:18:51,220
Did Lu Yuan eat tube popsicles too?

330
00:18:52,620 --> 00:18:53,780
Did he tell you

331
00:18:54,540 --> 00:18:56,540
who his supplier

332
00:18:56,540 --> 00:18:57,740
actually was?

333
00:18:57,740 --> 00:18:58,900
No, really.

334
00:18:58,900 --> 00:19:00,220
He never told me

335
00:19:00,220 --> 00:19:01,500
who his supplier was.

336
00:19:01,500 --> 00:19:02,460
I swear,

337
00:19:02,460 --> 00:19:04,060
never.

338
00:19:04,060 --> 00:19:05,100
I never expected

339
00:19:05,100 --> 00:19:06,500
the victim to be Lu Yuan.

340
00:19:07,780 --> 00:19:11,110
Looking at Guo Liansheng,
it really doesn't seem like he's lying.

341
00:19:12,300 --> 00:19:13,140
Big guy.

342
00:19:14,060 --> 00:19:15,620
This is Lu Yuan's pager number.

343
00:19:15,620 --> 00:19:17,620
Go check the call records immediately.

344
00:19:17,620 --> 00:19:18,700
Okay.

345
00:19:18,700 --> 00:19:20,060
Chief Liu,

346
00:19:20,060 --> 00:19:21,020
I suggest

347
00:19:21,020 --> 00:19:22,100
we search the whole town

348
00:19:22,100 --> 00:19:23,420
for red sedans.

349
00:19:23,420 --> 00:19:26,020
And we need Guo Liansheng's cooperation

350
00:19:26,020 --> 00:19:28,260
to create a composite sketch of Lu Yuan.

351
00:19:28,260 --> 00:19:29,500
Conditions here

352
00:19:29,500 --> 00:19:30,940
are too limited.

353
00:19:30,940 --> 00:19:32,220
We can't find a sketch artist.

354
00:19:32,220 --> 00:19:34,020
I'll coordinate with the municipal PSB.

355
00:19:34,020 --> 00:19:35,500
We'll send him there for the sketch.

356
00:19:35,500 --> 00:19:37,260
That would be great.

357
00:19:37,260 --> 00:19:38,740
Once we have Lu Yuan's sketch

358
00:19:38,740 --> 00:19:40,540
and find out his real identity,

359
00:19:40,540 --> 00:19:43,460
we'll be one step closer

360
00:19:43,460 --> 00:19:44,580
to the truth of this case.

361
00:20:27,500 --> 00:20:30,980
(One year ago)

362
00:20:33,890 --> 00:20:34,740
Help.

363
00:20:34,740 --> 00:20:35,580
Liang.

364
00:20:36,300 --> 00:20:37,220
Help...

365
00:20:39,820 --> 00:20:40,660
He's alive.

366
00:20:41,460 --> 00:20:42,300
Pull him up!

367
00:20:48,580 --> 00:20:49,420
Let me go.

368
00:20:58,420 --> 00:20:59,420
I won.

369
00:21:00,740 --> 00:21:01,740
I'm done.

370
00:21:01,740 --> 00:21:02,580
Alright.

371
00:21:02,980 --> 00:21:03,980
Stop wailing.

372
00:21:14,820 --> 00:21:16,180
Liang...

373
00:21:16,180 --> 00:21:17,220
Liang, I beg you.

374
00:21:17,340 --> 00:21:19,340
Let me go, please.

375
00:21:19,340 --> 00:21:20,420
Let me go, Liang.

376
00:21:20,420 --> 00:21:22,660
Let go.

377
00:21:23,500 --> 00:21:24,500
Don't freaking beg me.

378
00:21:25,140 --> 00:21:26,220
Listen here, Huo Kaiming.

379
00:21:27,100 --> 00:21:28,020
Your wife took

380
00:21:28,020 --> 00:21:29,220
250,000 from me.

381
00:21:30,020 --> 00:21:31,540
That was the price for your life.

382
00:21:31,540 --> 00:21:32,940
But now that you're alive,

383
00:21:33,940 --> 00:21:34,900
don't you have to give

384
00:21:34,900 --> 00:21:36,180
that 250,000 back to me?

385
00:21:36,700 --> 00:21:37,580
Liang,

386
00:21:37,580 --> 00:21:38,700
I beg you,

387
00:21:38,700 --> 00:21:39,540
I beg you...

388
00:21:39,540 --> 00:21:41,100
Don't beg me.

389
00:21:41,100 --> 00:21:42,500
I'm begging you, Mr. Huo.

390
00:21:43,020 --> 00:21:44,220
I'm the victim here.

391
00:21:44,220 --> 00:21:46,220
You guys cheated me out of my money.

392
00:21:46,220 --> 00:21:47,180
You guys conned me.

393
00:21:47,180 --> 00:21:48,420
What would you do if you were me?

394
00:21:48,420 --> 00:21:50,340
I wouldn't dare con you, Liang.

395
00:21:50,500 --> 00:21:53,300
Yuqin must have thought I was dead,
that's why she took the money.

396
00:21:53,300 --> 00:21:54,900
She must have gone back to our hometown.

397
00:21:54,900 --> 00:21:55,980
Let me go find her.

398
00:21:55,980 --> 00:21:57,540
I'll bring her back from home

399
00:21:57,540 --> 00:21:59,500
and give the money
back to you, okay, Liang?

400
00:21:59,500 --> 00:22:00,700
Huo Kaiming,

401
00:22:00,700 --> 00:22:02,980
can you clear your head for a second?

402
00:22:02,980 --> 00:22:05,420
Jiao Yuqin conned you too.

403
00:22:05,420 --> 00:22:07,660
You think after she conned you,
she'd go home and wait for you,

404
00:22:07,660 --> 00:22:10,020
just waiting for you to come back
and take the money back?

405
00:22:10,260 --> 00:22:11,140
No.

406
00:22:11,140 --> 00:22:12,260
Liang,

407
00:22:12,260 --> 00:22:13,500
Yuqin wouldn't lie to me.

408
00:22:13,500 --> 00:22:14,440
She wouldn't lie to me.

409
00:22:14,860 --> 00:22:17,780
She's pregnant with my child.

410
00:22:17,780 --> 00:22:18,710
She wouldn't lie to me.

411
00:22:20,720 --> 00:22:21,740
I didn't see that coming.

412
00:22:22,210 --> 00:22:23,740
You're quite the romantic, aren't you?

413
00:22:24,780 --> 00:22:25,780
Fine.

414
00:22:25,870 --> 00:22:27,900
You know, I'm a reasonable man too.

415
00:22:28,500 --> 00:22:29,340
Come here.

416
00:22:33,500 --> 00:22:35,460
Look, I have an IOU here.

417
00:22:35,460 --> 00:22:37,580
Put your thumbprint on it,

418
00:22:37,580 --> 00:22:38,710
and I'll let you go find her.

419
00:22:42,060 --> 00:22:43,580
(IOU)

420
00:22:43,580 --> 00:22:45,090
Liang, three days?

421
00:22:45,340 --> 00:22:46,340
That's too short.

422
00:22:54,180 --> 00:22:56,020
I'm giving you three days.

423
00:22:56,020 --> 00:22:57,620
Find this person for me,

424
00:22:57,620 --> 00:22:58,700
and get my 250,000

425
00:22:58,700 --> 00:22:59,860
back for me.

426
00:22:59,970 --> 00:23:01,480
I'm a man of my word.

427
00:23:04,420 --> 00:23:05,460
Here's your travel money.

428
00:23:05,460 --> 00:23:06,300
Now get lost.

429
00:23:08,060 --> 00:23:08,900
Get out.

430
00:23:13,500 --> 00:23:17,560
(Yunchuan)

431
00:23:17,560 --> 00:23:18,410
Excuse me, sir.

432
00:23:18,980 --> 00:23:20,050
Could I ask you something?

433
00:23:20,540 --> 00:23:22,700
Is there someone
named Jiao Yuqin in this village?

434
00:23:22,700 --> 00:23:23,700
Jiao Yuqin?

435
00:23:25,060 --> 00:23:27,580
Her whole family died over a decade ago.

436
00:23:27,580 --> 00:23:30,380
She was married off
when she was seventeen.

437
00:23:30,380 --> 00:23:32,180
Married off at seventeen?

438
00:23:32,180 --> 00:23:33,020
That's right.

439
00:23:33,500 --> 00:23:34,420
That's impossible.

440
00:23:36,740 --> 00:23:39,190
Is there anyone else
with the same name, another Jiao Yuqin?

441
00:23:39,190 --> 00:23:40,070
No.

442
00:23:40,070 --> 00:23:40,940
Just her.

443
00:23:41,420 --> 00:23:43,140
Do you know

444
00:23:43,140 --> 00:23:44,420
where she moved to?

445
00:23:44,420 --> 00:23:45,260
No idea.

446
00:23:46,220 --> 00:23:47,540
Go ask over there.

447
00:23:51,140 --> 00:23:52,100
Jiao Yuqin!

448
00:23:54,140 --> 00:23:55,140
Jiao Yuqin!

449
00:23:56,940 --> 00:23:58,580
Jiao Yuqin!

450
00:23:58,580 --> 00:23:59,420
Who are you?

451
00:24:01,420 --> 00:24:02,700
Does Jiao Yuqin live here?

452
00:24:02,700 --> 00:24:03,780
What do you want with her?

453
00:24:05,500 --> 00:24:06,340
Jiao Yuqin.

454
00:24:06,350 --> 00:24:07,640
- What are you doing?
- Jiao Yuqin!

455
00:24:07,650 --> 00:24:09,780
- What are you doing?
- Jiao Yuqin!

456
00:24:09,780 --> 00:24:11,260
It's Huo Kaiming.

457
00:24:11,260 --> 00:24:12,220
What are you doing? This is my house!

458
00:24:12,220 --> 00:24:13,600
- Jiao Yuqin!
- Don't you dare start anything!

459
00:24:14,340 --> 00:24:15,220
Jiao Yuqin!

460
00:24:15,220 --> 00:24:16,110
Come out!

461
00:24:16,110 --> 00:24:17,470
- Jiao Yuqin, are you there?
- What do you think you're doing?

462
00:24:17,550 --> 00:24:19,340
Sir, I'm not here to cause trouble.

463
00:24:19,340 --> 00:24:20,540
I'm just looking for Jiao Yuqin.

464
00:24:20,540 --> 00:24:21,820
Tell her to come out and talk to me.

465
00:24:21,820 --> 00:24:22,780
What's your relationship with her?

466
00:24:22,780 --> 00:24:24,220
I'm her husband.

467
00:24:24,220 --> 00:24:25,420
She's even pregnant with my child.

468
00:24:25,420 --> 00:24:26,740
That's why I'm so desperate to find her.

469
00:24:26,740 --> 00:24:27,940
That wretched woman.

470
00:24:27,940 --> 00:24:29,460
She ran off after being
married to me for six months.

471
00:24:29,460 --> 00:24:30,900
And she's pregnant with your child?

472
00:24:30,900 --> 00:24:32,060
Don't be so hasty.

473
00:24:32,060 --> 00:24:32,900
No, no.

474
00:24:33,420 --> 00:24:34,320
That's impossible.

475
00:24:34,320 --> 00:24:35,390
She's my wife.

476
00:24:35,390 --> 00:24:36,620
How could she have married you?

477
00:24:37,260 --> 00:24:38,980
When are you talking about?

478
00:24:38,980 --> 00:24:40,500
That was several years ago.

479
00:24:40,500 --> 00:24:41,420
Well, that's even more wrong.

480
00:24:41,420 --> 00:24:42,860
Even more wrong.

481
00:24:42,860 --> 00:24:43,820
Sir,

482
00:24:46,090 --> 00:24:47,020
take a look.

483
00:24:47,020 --> 00:24:48,410
Is this the woman you're talking about?

484
00:24:49,820 --> 00:24:51,420
This isn't Jiao Yuqin.

485
00:24:53,740 --> 00:24:55,540
This one is Jiao Yuqin.

486
00:24:56,460 --> 00:24:57,740
Look closely.

487
00:24:57,740 --> 00:24:58,860
This is Jiao Yuqin.

488
00:25:00,220 --> 00:25:01,220
Then, who is she?

489
00:25:01,220 --> 00:25:02,500
Who is she?

490
00:25:02,500 --> 00:25:03,460
How should I know?

491
00:25:04,220 --> 00:25:05,380
I think

492
00:25:05,380 --> 00:25:06,620
you're just like her.

493
00:25:06,620 --> 00:25:08,180
You're both fools.

494
00:25:09,940 --> 00:25:10,780
Yuqin,

495
00:25:10,780 --> 00:25:12,340
you must have been conned.

496
00:25:18,420 --> 00:25:19,260
Liars,

497
00:25:20,980 --> 00:25:22,380
go to heck.

498
00:25:24,820 --> 00:25:30,340
(Glycerol)

499
00:25:32,220 --> 00:25:33,060
Chief Liu,

500
00:25:34,660 --> 00:25:37,420
our leads kept going cold before.

501
00:25:37,420 --> 00:25:40,140
But we've finally made some progress.

502
00:25:40,140 --> 00:25:41,380
Limin found

503
00:25:41,380 --> 00:25:42,660
Lu Yuan's call records.

504
00:25:44,180 --> 00:25:45,700
Those guys selling Peidun Cough Syrup

505
00:25:45,700 --> 00:25:47,020
won't be able to escape now.

506
00:25:48,060 --> 00:25:48,940
Let's hope so.

507
00:25:49,860 --> 00:25:51,620
During this time,

508
00:25:51,620 --> 00:25:52,660
you've worked hard.

509
00:25:55,140 --> 00:25:56,420
Chief Liu,

510
00:25:58,300 --> 00:26:01,780
if there's anything I did

511
00:26:01,780 --> 00:26:02,820
wrong before,

512
00:26:04,700 --> 00:26:05,580
please don't mind.

513
00:26:07,380 --> 00:26:09,900
I did have
some opinions about you at first.

514
00:26:09,900 --> 00:26:12,940
Especially when I first arrived in town,
that time the truck driver's father

515
00:26:12,940 --> 00:26:13,980
came to ask you for help.

516
00:26:15,450 --> 00:26:16,340
Hongbing,

517
00:26:16,340 --> 00:26:17,420
it's just a small token.

518
00:26:18,100 --> 00:26:19,300
About my son's matter,

519
00:26:19,300 --> 00:26:20,420
please help us out.

520
00:26:21,940 --> 00:26:23,370
(Chunghwa Cigarettes)
This is way too blatant.

521
00:26:23,780 --> 00:26:24,820
This is yours, right?

522
00:26:26,380 --> 00:26:27,620
Keep the cigarettes,

523
00:26:27,620 --> 00:26:28,900
but return the money to me.

524
00:26:28,900 --> 00:26:30,110
I'll get the money for you right now.

525
00:26:32,320 --> 00:26:34,180
It would be so much easier
to just take the money.

526
00:26:34,180 --> 00:26:35,340
It would save you a trip.

527
00:26:35,340 --> 00:26:36,980
Then, the nature of this would change.

528
00:26:39,020 --> 00:26:40,060
Director Chen,

529
00:26:40,270 --> 00:26:41,710
count it. It's exactly 1,200 yuan.

530
00:26:41,900 --> 00:26:43,940
Later, when I was
questioning the truck driver,

531
00:26:43,940 --> 00:26:47,220
and the detention center director
asked me to bring the receipt to you,

532
00:26:47,220 --> 00:26:48,570
I realized I had misunderstood you.

533
00:26:48,580 --> 00:26:50,300
(Receipt: Received 1,200 yuan
from Chen Hongbing)

534
00:26:50,300 --> 00:26:51,170
1,200?

535
00:26:51,370 --> 00:26:52,220
Yes.

536
00:26:52,220 --> 00:26:53,380
I assume

537
00:26:53,380 --> 00:26:55,370
the family member
went to see Director Chen again.

538
00:26:55,940 --> 00:26:57,780
Does he run into this often?

539
00:26:57,780 --> 00:26:58,700
Occasionally.

540
00:26:58,700 --> 00:26:59,660
Sometimes,

541
00:26:59,660 --> 00:27:01,660
when the criminals' families run
out of options,

542
00:27:01,660 --> 00:27:03,030
they all go to see Director Chen.

543
00:27:03,200 --> 00:27:04,060
Why doesn't he

544
00:27:04,060 --> 00:27:05,700
just return the money directly to them?

545
00:27:05,700 --> 00:27:08,060
He will return it directly if he can.

546
00:27:08,060 --> 00:27:09,700
But for some families,

547
00:27:09,700 --> 00:27:11,140
if you return the money,

548
00:27:11,140 --> 00:27:12,180
they will think

549
00:27:12,180 --> 00:27:13,780
it's because they didn't give enough.

550
00:27:13,780 --> 00:27:17,220
And they'll turn around
and buy even more expensive gifts.

551
00:27:17,220 --> 00:27:18,420
When that happens,

552
00:27:18,420 --> 00:27:20,260
Director Chen usually deposits the money

553
00:27:20,260 --> 00:27:22,500
directly into the suspect's account.

554
00:27:23,820 --> 00:27:25,220
Handling cases here
at the grassroots level

555
00:27:25,220 --> 00:27:27,540
is indeed different
from how we do it in the city.

556
00:27:27,540 --> 00:27:29,020
I've been learning as well.

557
00:27:29,020 --> 00:27:31,010
You've worked hard
during this time, Director Chen.

558
00:27:31,620 --> 00:27:34,380
We're veteran
police officers, aren't we?

559
00:27:34,380 --> 00:27:35,740
It's only right

560
00:27:35,740 --> 00:27:36,740
doing our duty.

561
00:27:38,100 --> 00:27:39,940
I

562
00:27:39,940 --> 00:27:42,060
don't like owing anyone favors.

563
00:27:42,060 --> 00:27:43,180
You and your wife

564
00:27:43,180 --> 00:27:44,580
have taken good care of me.

565
00:27:44,580 --> 00:27:46,020
Even though I didn't want to,
I still owe you.

566
00:27:46,020 --> 00:27:47,700
Don't worry about favors.

567
00:27:48,720 --> 00:27:50,180
By the way,
I've been busy these past few days

568
00:27:50,180 --> 00:27:51,940
and haven't had a chance to tell you.

569
00:27:52,080 --> 00:27:54,020
I've already submitted
Gao Ying's paperwork.

570
00:27:54,380 --> 00:27:56,740
I'll let you know
once the municipal PSB gets back to us.

571
00:28:01,460 --> 00:28:02,300
Thank you.

572
00:28:30,340 --> 00:28:33,060
(Elegant Magnolia Powder Cream)

573
00:28:48,620 --> 00:28:49,460
Chief Liu,

574
00:28:49,900 --> 00:28:50,900
what brings you here?

575
00:28:50,900 --> 00:28:52,500
Director Chen.

576
00:28:52,500 --> 00:28:54,540
What is this?

577
00:28:54,540 --> 00:28:57,420
This is cosmetics I bought for your wife
the last time I went back to the city.

578
00:28:57,420 --> 00:28:58,540
Please give it to Mrs. Chen for me.

579
00:28:58,540 --> 00:28:59,620
Don't, Chief Liu.

580
00:28:59,620 --> 00:29:01,140
Look at you.

581
00:29:01,140 --> 00:29:01,980
Now that you're here,

582
00:29:01,980 --> 00:29:03,220
you can't just leave.

583
00:29:03,220 --> 00:29:04,060
Come inside.

584
00:29:04,820 --> 00:29:05,930
This doesn't seem appropriate.

585
00:29:05,940 --> 00:29:06,780
Come on in.

586
00:29:06,780 --> 00:29:07,620
Ding Yue,

587
00:29:07,890 --> 00:29:08,740
look who's here.

588
00:29:08,740 --> 00:29:09,580
Chief Liu is here.

589
00:29:10,340 --> 00:29:11,220
Na,

590
00:29:11,220 --> 00:29:13,150
have some of these
scrambled eggs with tomatoes.

591
00:29:13,270 --> 00:29:14,180
Give them a try.

592
00:29:14,180 --> 00:29:15,860
I'm not particularly good at cooking.

593
00:29:15,860 --> 00:29:17,140
I hope they're to your liking.

594
00:29:23,020 --> 00:29:25,320
It's been a long time since I've had
this kind of home-cooked flavor.

595
00:29:25,320 --> 00:29:26,260
It's delicious.

596
00:29:26,260 --> 00:29:27,420
If you like it,

597
00:29:27,420 --> 00:29:28,300
then come over often.

598
00:29:28,300 --> 00:29:30,970
You can't eat the food at
the guesthouse every day, right?

599
00:29:30,970 --> 00:29:31,820
Come often.

600
00:29:32,260 --> 00:29:33,100
Thank you.

601
00:29:33,740 --> 00:29:34,940
I'd rather not be a bother.

602
00:29:39,100 --> 00:29:40,700
It's no trouble at all.

603
00:29:44,900 --> 00:29:46,020
Here.

604
00:29:46,020 --> 00:29:46,980
Thank you.

605
00:29:48,340 --> 00:29:50,060
Thanks too.

606
00:29:50,060 --> 00:29:50,900
Have some eggs.

607
00:29:52,460 --> 00:29:53,380
Hongbing.

608
00:29:54,020 --> 00:29:54,860
Hongbing.

609
00:29:55,180 --> 00:29:56,770
- Dad, why are you awake?
- Give me...

610
00:29:56,860 --> 00:29:57,860
Give me a bath.

611
00:29:57,860 --> 00:29:58,940
Scrub my back.

612
00:29:58,940 --> 00:30:00,260
A bath?

613
00:30:00,260 --> 00:30:02,100
Didn't I just wash you at noon?

614
00:30:03,220 --> 00:30:04,340
When did we do that?

615
00:30:06,020 --> 00:30:07,340
Alright.

616
00:30:07,340 --> 00:30:09,220
I'll be right there.

617
00:30:09,220 --> 00:30:11,300
You guys go ahead and eat.

618
00:30:11,300 --> 00:30:12,140
Come on.

619
00:30:12,140 --> 00:30:12,980
Dad.

620
00:30:14,060 --> 00:30:15,940
Sit down.

621
00:30:15,940 --> 00:30:17,340
You're really big on hygiene, aren't you?

622
00:30:17,340 --> 00:30:18,210
Tell me about it.

623
00:30:18,450 --> 00:30:19,300
It's fine.

624
00:30:19,300 --> 00:30:21,380
The old man has moments
of clarity and confusion.

625
00:30:21,380 --> 00:30:22,420
Eat more vegetables.

626
00:30:22,420 --> 00:30:23,420
And this tofu.

627
00:30:23,420 --> 00:30:24,410
It's all quite delicious.

628
00:30:36,700 --> 00:30:37,540
Na,

629
00:30:38,460 --> 00:30:39,300
there's something

630
00:30:40,100 --> 00:30:42,180
I've been wanting to ask you.

631
00:30:43,780 --> 00:30:45,060
This illness of yours,

632
00:30:45,060 --> 00:30:46,500
it's been a while, right?

633
00:30:46,500 --> 00:30:47,980
Do you know what it is yourself?

634
00:30:49,900 --> 00:30:50,820
Illness?

635
00:30:50,820 --> 00:30:52,020
I don't have any illness.

636
00:30:53,740 --> 00:30:55,300
I saw the needle marks

637
00:30:55,300 --> 00:30:56,580
from the IV on your arm.

638
00:30:56,580 --> 00:30:57,520
They've already scarred.

639
00:30:58,260 --> 00:31:00,380
With IV drips at this frequency,

640
00:31:00,380 --> 00:31:02,460
it must be an immune system issue.

641
00:31:05,700 --> 00:31:06,740
I saw it that day

642
00:31:06,740 --> 00:31:08,340
when I was giving you the IV.

643
00:31:10,340 --> 00:31:11,380
Mrs. Chen,

644
00:31:11,380 --> 00:31:13,020
about this matter,

645
00:31:13,020 --> 00:31:14,300
did you tell Director Chen?

646
00:31:15,660 --> 00:31:18,020
Though we don't have
discipline like you police,

647
00:31:18,020 --> 00:31:19,340
we don't discuss

648
00:31:19,340 --> 00:31:20,660
patient matters with others.

649
00:31:21,460 --> 00:31:22,340
Don't worry.

650
00:31:24,260 --> 00:31:25,300
Thank you.

651
00:31:26,660 --> 00:31:29,260
I didn't mean anything else by it.

652
00:31:29,260 --> 00:31:30,820
I just wanted to remind you

653
00:31:30,820 --> 00:31:32,580
that your health is what matters most.

654
00:31:32,580 --> 00:31:34,260
Don't let your work

655
00:31:34,260 --> 00:31:35,300
compromise your health.

656
00:31:53,460 --> 00:31:54,340
Director Chen,

657
00:31:54,340 --> 00:31:55,180
Mrs. Chen,

658
00:31:55,860 --> 00:31:58,860
actually, there's something
I've been holding in for a long time.

659
00:31:58,860 --> 00:32:00,020
I didn't know

660
00:32:00,020 --> 00:32:01,220
if I should tell you.

661
00:32:03,060 --> 00:32:03,900
What is it?

662
00:32:03,900 --> 00:32:05,340
Tell us.

663
00:32:05,340 --> 00:32:06,780
My illness

664
00:32:06,780 --> 00:32:07,740
is untreatable now.

665
00:32:09,620 --> 00:32:10,940
What illness is untreatable?

666
00:32:10,940 --> 00:32:11,780
Yes, what is it?

667
00:32:12,180 --> 00:32:13,580
Lymphoma.

668
00:32:13,580 --> 00:32:15,220
It had already spread when it was found.

669
00:32:16,780 --> 00:32:17,620
That day,

670
00:32:18,380 --> 00:32:20,180
I thought I would die in the guesthouse.

671
00:32:22,220 --> 00:32:23,060
But you came.

672
00:32:24,700 --> 00:32:26,620
I felt that having family
is truly wonderful.

673
00:32:35,220 --> 00:32:36,060
It's okay.

674
00:32:38,300 --> 00:32:39,140
Chief Liu,

675
00:32:39,940 --> 00:32:40,780
don't be sad.

676
00:32:41,500 --> 00:32:42,580
Go back to the city

677
00:32:42,580 --> 00:32:43,420
and recover properly.

678
00:32:44,460 --> 00:32:46,340
Any progress on the case here,

679
00:32:46,340 --> 00:32:47,640
I will report to you at any time.

680
00:32:48,820 --> 00:32:50,460
Director Chen, don't try to persuade me.

681
00:32:51,380 --> 00:32:52,460
This should be

682
00:32:52,460 --> 00:32:53,740
the last case I take.

683
00:32:53,740 --> 00:32:55,020
No matter what,

684
00:32:55,020 --> 00:32:56,140
I have to see it through.

685
00:32:57,260 --> 00:32:58,900
Also,

686
00:32:58,900 --> 00:33:00,300
please keep this a secret for me.

687
00:33:01,660 --> 00:33:03,860
Let me fully enjoy the joy of working.

688
00:33:05,900 --> 00:33:06,740
Understood.

689
00:33:22,900 --> 00:33:23,860
This way.

690
00:33:31,460 --> 00:33:32,460
Last night,

691
00:33:32,460 --> 00:33:34,300
in the wasteland outside Fengyang Town,

692
00:33:34,300 --> 00:33:37,220
another body-burning homicide occurred.

693
00:33:37,220 --> 00:33:39,740
According to the police investigation,
the suspect

694
00:33:39,740 --> 00:33:41,420
was driving a red car.

695
00:33:42,140 --> 00:33:43,220
Everyone,

696
00:33:43,220 --> 00:33:45,100
if you spot a suspicious red vehicle,

697
00:33:45,100 --> 00:33:46,220
please contact this station.

698
00:33:49,540 --> 00:33:50,380
What's wrong?

699
00:33:52,660 --> 00:33:54,660
Did something happen up ahead?

700
00:33:54,660 --> 00:33:56,020
It's nothing.

701
00:33:56,020 --> 00:33:57,140
You just finished dialysis.

702
00:33:57,140 --> 00:33:58,100
Rest a bit more.

703
00:34:00,500 --> 00:34:01,340
Hello.

704
00:34:01,720 --> 00:34:03,420
Registration
and driver's license, please.

705
00:34:32,900 --> 00:34:42,820
(Yingxiong Roller Skating Rink)

706
00:35:14,410 --> 00:35:16,140
Chen Hui.

707
00:35:16,520 --> 00:35:17,860
There seems to be someone outside.

708
00:36:10,060 --> 00:36:12,300
Chen Hui!

709
00:36:12,300 --> 00:36:13,140
Songge!

710
00:36:49,500 --> 00:36:55,580
♪I always thought
once we see the full picture♪

711
00:36:56,900 --> 00:37:02,740
♪We could understand
each other with empathy♪

712
00:37:04,300 --> 00:37:10,740
♪I always thought
the path we never took♪

713
00:37:11,460 --> 00:37:17,060
♪Must have had more beautiful scenery♪

714
00:37:19,140 --> 00:37:25,180
♪I always thought
once we see the full picture♪

715
00:37:26,460 --> 00:37:32,180
♪We could understand
each other with empathy♪

716
00:37:33,940 --> 00:37:40,260
♪I always thought
the path we never took♪

717
00:37:40,900 --> 00:37:46,700
♪Must have had more beautiful scenery♪

718
00:37:48,420 --> 00:37:51,340
♪Keep moving forward
and don't look back♪

719
00:37:52,180 --> 00:37:55,420
♪The shore is only reached
by the road ahead♪

720
00:37:55,860 --> 00:37:58,540
♪Too much debt has accumulated♪

721
00:37:59,300 --> 00:38:02,300
♪Lit night♪

722
00:38:03,460 --> 00:38:06,660
♪Unfortunately, the breeze in town♪

723
00:38:07,140 --> 00:38:10,140
♪Can no longer catch up to the children♪

724
00:38:10,580 --> 00:38:13,580
♪Times have changed♪

725
00:38:14,300 --> 00:38:16,260
♪Now, everything♪

726
00:38:17,300 --> 00:38:20,340
♪Is no longer what it used to be♪

